Scottburgh SAPS are appealing for help in identifying the next of kin of a teenage pedestrian who was fatally wounded in a collision along the northbound lane in Sezela. Captain Adam Francis, Scottburgh SAPS communication officer, said that the incident occurred on Monday, 21 September, at approximately 4.30pm. He said: “A male pedestrian aged between 12 and 16 years of age was killed in a motor vehicle collision on the north bound lane in Sezela. An appeal is made to the next of kin or anyone else who could assist in tracing the family of the deceased.” Anyone with any information is urged to contact Detective Warrant Officer Vis Moodley of Scottburgh Detective Service on 039 978 1900.